      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your product image is trying to be a little too cheeky and is just not respecting the title text's space. Maybe it's feeling a bit too confident, like a young goblin trying to impress the village folk. Let's give it a gentle nudge with some responsive design magic.\n\nTry adding a media query to your CSS to specifically target mobile screens. This way, we can make sure our goblin image doesn't overshadow the title text when the shop is visited by those on smaller screens. Here's a snippet to get you started:\n\n```css\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  .product-header {\n    flex-direction: row;\n    align-items: center;\n  }\n\n  .product-image {\n    margin-right: 10px;\n  }\n\n  .product-title {\n    margin-top: 0;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis should help your product image and title text to get along better on mobile devices. Remember, even the most mischievous goblins need a little help sometimes!",
